<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,151,356]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,304,151,176]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe north to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[602,690,151,175]" name="Finland" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Finland</collectingCountry>
, present in 
<collectingCountry box="[822,918,151,175]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">England</collectingCountry>
, southward absent from the Balkan Peninsula and 
<collectingCountry box="[198,278,188,212]" name="Turkey" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich" box="[292,459,188,212]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Westrich, P. (1989) Die Wildbienen Baden-Wurttembergs. Band. 1 und 2. Eugen Ulmer Verlag, Stuttgart, 972 pp." type="book" year="1989">
Westrich 
<number box="[400,459,188,212]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1989.0">1989</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke" box="[470,636,188,212]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Warncke, K. (1992) Die Westpalaarktischen Arten der Bienengattung Sphecodes Latr. (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Halictinae). Bericht der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft Augsburg, 52, 9 - 64." type="journal article" year="1992">
Warncke 
<number box="[576,636,188,212]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,151,356]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,223,248]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Biology.</emphasis>
Very rare species of sandy wetlands, in most countries endangered or extinct. The distribution is much weaker than in the past. The host is 
<taxonomicName box="[553,809,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zonulum">
<emphasis box="[553,809,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Lasioglossum zonulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, recorded in the literature (
<bibRefCitation author="Bluthgen" box="[1114,1284,260,284]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Bluthgen, P. (1934) Die Wirte der Palaarktischen Sphecodes - Arten. Zeitschrift Wissenschaftlicher Insekten-Biologie, 27, 33 - 42, 61 - 66. Bluthgen, P. (1935) Halictus, Nomioides und Sphecodes, pp. 360 - 367. In: Popov, V. V. (ed.) Beitrage zur Bienenfauna von Tadzhikistan. Trudy Tajikskoy Bazy Akademie Nauk SSSR, 5, 1 - 408." type="book chapter" year="1934">
Blüthgen 
<number box="[1225,1284,260,284]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1934.0">1934</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, Yates 
<number box="[1363,1423,260,284]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2002.0">2002</number>
), the first author also recorded 
<taxonomicName box="[490,724,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="compressus">
<emphasis box="[490,724,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Halictus compressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[740,930,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadricinctus">
<emphasis box="[740,930,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">H. quadricinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[988,1257,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prasinum">
<emphasis box="[988,1257,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Lasioglossum prasinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as likely hosts. More recently, parasitation only in nests of 
<taxonomicName box="[637,762,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zonulum">
<emphasis box="[637,762,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">L. zonulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was observed (M. Herrmann, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
